gomodel:SYNGO_1904  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 1: PRG-1 (gene PLPPR4) was mainly expressed on dendrites and colocalized with ProSAP2 (SHANK3) and Homer, but not Gephyrin (GPHN). Subcellular fractionation of mouse cerebral cortex revealed PRG-1 within the PSD. PRG-1 was detected in this fraction but not in the presynaptic vesicle fraction (SC+CSV).\n\n\"Finally, localization at the ultrastructural level revealed DAB-reaction product, indicating PRG-1 immunolabeling exclusively at postsynaptic structures of asymmetric synapses of CA1 pyramidal cells and silver-enhanced immunogold signal of PRG-1 bordering the synaptic cleft (Figure 1D).\"\n\nBased on the known transmembrane topology of this protein, \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was selected.. Experimental description: \"Mice were anesthetized (0.5% ketamine i.p.) and transcardially perfused with 4% PFA for IHC and DIG in situ.\" p. 1233\n\nantibody:\nPRG-1 (1:1500; custom-made antibody against aa 624-637, NP_808332) (this refseq protein accession matches uniprot sp|Q7TME0|PLPR4_MOUSE)" , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099061 replaced by GO:0098839" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9377-7414" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9681-3318" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0269-0311" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9880-1214" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_1904" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

